goals.question: What is the relationship between age and population?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['year'], data_grouped['people'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Population'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sex_counts = data.groupby('sex')['people'].sum()
    sex_counts.index = ['Male', 'Female']
    ax = sex_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'red'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of sex in the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Sex')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    ax.legend(['People'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('age_group')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    ax = data_grouped.plot.bar(x='age_group', y='people', legend=False)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of age groups in the population?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Age Group")
    plt.ylabel("Number of People")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['age'], data['people'], c=data['sex'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between age and population?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Sex")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
